05:14.024 --> 05:16.470
<i>♪ That I'm irresponsibly ♪</i>

05:16.563 --> 05:19.001
<i>♪ mad for you ♪</i>

05:19.126 --> 05:21.165
♪♪

05:21.274 --> 05:24.446
<i>♪ Go on and call me ♪</i>

05:24.501 --> 05:26.251
<i>♪ unpredictable ♪</i>

05:26.314 --> 05:27.564
<i>♪ tell me that... ♪</i>

05:28.485 --> 05:30.485
<i>♪ I'm impractical ♪</i>

05:30.587 --> 05:32.345
<i>♪ rainbows ♪</i>

05:32.426 --> 05:36.626
<i>♪ I'm inclined to pursue ♪</i>

05:36.716 --> 05:39.571
<i>♪ you go ahead and call me ♪</i>

05:39.642 --> 05:41.845
<i>♪ irresponsible ♪</i>

05:41.892 --> 05:42.937
<i>♪ I admit ♪</i>

05:42.962 --> 05:45.751
<i>♪ I'm unreliable ♪</i>

05:45.798 --> 05:49.079
<i>♪ but it is undeniably true... ♪</i>

05:49.126 --> 05:50.165
sheriff Greene,

05:50.235 --> 05:52.689
<i>we found a piece of luggage
buried out front.</i>

05:52.766 --> 05:55.666
<i>It belongs to a...
Audrey Decody.</i>

05:55.731 --> 05:57.431
Don't move.
I'm coming down.

05:57.789 --> 05:59.657
I hate to steal
anyone's thunder,

05:59.771 --> 06:02.369
but I've got that
beat by a mile.

06:02.568 --> 06:06.454
♪♪

06:06.478 --> 06:09.532
♪♪

06:14.954 --> 06:18.767
♪♪

06:18.892 --> 06:22.696
♪♪

06:36.267 --> 06:38.307
This isn't real.

06:40.130 --> 06:42.460
This isn't happening.

06:42.931 --> 06:45.423
I know;
I feel the same way.

06:45.931 --> 06:49.181
I mean, even though
I've thought these things

06:49.415 --> 06:53.236
and wondered about all this
stuff for so long, it just...

06:54.540 --> 06:57.173
Doesn't seem possible.

06:58.642 --> 07:01.431
I'm so sorry, Emma.

07:02.556 --> 07:06.204
I never wanted to bring you
anything but happiness.

07:06.782 --> 07:08.861
It's not your fault.

07:09.392 --> 07:12.368
You didn't bring Norman
into my life.

07:16.423 --> 07:18.837
He was so sweet when I met him.

07:19.337 --> 07:22.415
Norman is sweet, he's...
He's just out of his mind.

07:24.681 --> 07:26.634
That doesn't make it
better for me.

07:26.782 --> 07:29.112
♪♪

07:29.321 --> 07:31.071
Of course not.

07:34.316 --> 07:35.616
I need to go home.

07:35.704 --> 07:36.874
Emma, please, don't, please,

07:36.899 --> 07:38.595
just stay here with me, please.

07:38.675 --> 07:40.151
♪♪ <i>Somber orchestration</i>

07:40.246 --> 07:41.831
Please, don't go.

07:42.001 --> 07:47.560
♪♪

07:47.880 --> 07:50.193
I'll stay to take care
of my mother's body.

07:50.342 --> 07:52.380
♪♪

07:52.532 --> 07:55.982
But I don't know if we're gonna
make it through this, Dylan.

07:57.123 --> 07:59.310
I can't promise you that.

07:59.958 --> 08:01.724
I understand.

08:02.653 --> 08:04.036
And please don't talk to me

08:04.060 --> 08:05.427
about having
sympathy for Norman.

08:05.474 --> 08:06.701
If I ever lay eyes on him again,

08:06.725 --> 08:08.013
I might just kill him.

08:08.560 --> 08:09.919
Okay.

08:10.249 --> 08:13.249
♪♪ <i>Eerie music</i>

08:16.654 --> 08:20.505
I need the handcuffs off.
He's got documents to sign.

08:26.068 --> 08:27.365
I'll be right outside.

08:27.460 --> 08:29.513
What a relief.

08:35.466 --> 08:37.607
Are they treating you all right?

08:38.044 --> 08:41.013
If I said they weren't,
could you get me out?

08:41.365 --> 08:45.326
I'm sorry, Norman,
this is gonna be a tough road.

08:47.832 --> 08:49.622
So what happens now?

08:49.902 --> 08:52.451
Well, tomorrow you have
your preliminary hearing.

08:52.705 --> 08:55.740
The judge has to decide whether
to take the case to trial,

08:55.852 --> 08:57.680
depending on
the state's evidence.

08:57.802 --> 09:00.107
It's a formality,
but from what I've seen,

09:00.177 --> 09:01.255
they're taking you to trial.

09:01.279 --> 09:03.787
Which is why we need to start
thinking about our approach.

09:03.849 --> 09:05.427
Oh, well, I didn't do it,

09:05.490 --> 09:07.279
so not guilty.

09:07.386 --> 09:08.646
I agree.

09:08.770 --> 09:09.870
You believe me?

09:10.037 --> 09:11.458
I agree with your approach.

09:11.564 --> 09:12.684
There are no light sentences

09:12.722 --> 09:14.488
when it comes to
serial homicide.

09:14.568 --> 09:16.622
But if you plead guilty,
the best we can hope for

09:16.697 --> 09:18.076
is to keep you alive.

09:18.209 --> 09:22.138
Multiple life sentences
in a maximum security prison.

09:22.396 --> 09:23.661
With your permission,

09:23.747 --> 09:25.877
I would like to aim
a little bit higher.

09:25.982 --> 09:28.408
Permission granted.
How?

09:30.247 --> 09:33.279
Not guilty
by reason of insanity.

09:34.714 --> 09:37.076
So I spend the rest of
my life in an institution?

09:37.138 --> 09:38.990
Probably, yes.

09:39.662 --> 09:40.662
I don't like it.

09:40.719 --> 09:41.787
I don't blame you.

09:41.964 --> 09:43.669
But I... I wasn't
in my right mind

09:43.694 --> 09:44.722
when they questioned me.

09:44.747 --> 09:46.708
I asked multiple times
for my medication.

09:46.775 --> 09:49.127
They never gave it to me.
And that sheriff Greene? It's...

09:49.263 --> 09:51.091
She hated me
the moment she met me.

09:51.185 --> 09:53.294
It's like I smelled bad
to her or something.

09:53.615 --> 09:55.032
It's weird.
She's so weird.

09:55.091 --> 09:56.193
It's inappropriate.

09:56.284 --> 09:57.724
Yeah, she messed up.

09:58.044 --> 09:59.294
She crossed the line.

09:59.365 --> 10:00.971
And I will make
a motion in court

10:01.029 --> 10:02.826
to suppress your confession
on the grounds that

10:02.850 --> 10:05.615
it was made during duress
and cognitive impairment.

10:05.657 --> 10:06.810
That's great.
I love that.

10:06.879 --> 10:08.724
But the state still has

10:08.814 --> 10:11.865
very strong physical evidence
against you, Norman.

10:12.232 --> 10:15.086
Look, we can take our chances
fighting it piece by piece,

10:15.169 --> 10:19.157
but you have a legitimately
strong insanity plea.

10:19.435 --> 10:21.747
Because my stepfather
locked me up

10:21.808 --> 10:23.338
in an institution?

10:23.429 --> 10:24.701
Sure.

10:24.997 --> 10:27.693
Also, because maybe
you needed to be there.

10:28.138 --> 10:31.052
Look, uh, your brother says

10:31.291 --> 10:33.872
you struggle with
multiple personalities.

10:34.083 --> 10:35.816
And Dylan's a doctor now?

10:35.951 --> 10:39.071
He didn't know
the proper term, but I do.

10:39.216 --> 10:42.349
Dissociative identity disorder:
Did.

10:42.732 --> 10:44.094
Do you know if you've ever been

10:44.189 --> 10:45.787
diagnosed with it?

10:45.984 --> 10:48.984
♪♪ <i>Gentle tense music...</i>

10:49.537 --> 10:50.987
Everyone

10:51.138 --> 10:53.489
has multiple personalities,
Julia.

10:53.599 --> 10:55.192
♪♪

10:55.396 --> 10:57.255
We pull out what we need
when we have to.

10:57.341 --> 10:58.996
That's not really
an answer, Norman.

10:59.052 --> 11:00.826
At least not one
I can use in court.

11:00.858 --> 11:03.122
Well, I was only
in pineview for two weeks.

11:03.202 --> 11:05.669
And I don't think anyone there
ever really understood me.

11:05.792 --> 11:07.615
Which is why
I think it's crucial

11:07.673 --> 11:09.403
that we have you evaluated now.

11:09.482 --> 11:10.880
I need to understand you

11:10.943 --> 11:12.521
to best figure out
how to help you.

11:12.644 --> 11:16.497
♪♪

11:16.759 --> 11:18.232
Are you a mother?

11:18.417 --> 11:20.719
♪♪

11:21.012 --> 11:22.037
No.

11:22.087 --> 11:23.341
- Do you want to be a mother?
- No.

11:23.365 --> 11:24.630
That's smart.

11:25.718 --> 11:28.853
'Cause you seem like
you like to succeed,

11:29.138 --> 11:30.154
to win.

11:30.294 --> 11:32.138
♪♪ <i>Gentle ominous music...</i>

11:32.333 --> 11:35.630
And being a mother is
an impossible job to win.

11:35.868 --> 11:39.630
♪♪

11:39.825 --> 11:43.668
♪♪

11:43.990 --> 11:47.443
We'll take it
one step at a time, okay?

11:48.828 --> 11:52.404
One step at a time
closer to hell?

11:52.899 --> 11:55.310
I don't believe in hell.

11:55.455 --> 11:58.904
♪♪

11:58.990 --> 12:01.841
♪♪

12:01.927 --> 12:03.310
Dad, i... i don't know.

12:03.404 --> 12:04.559
No, I don't want
you to come here.

12:04.583 --> 12:06.396
I want you to
be there with Katie.

12:06.590 --> 12:08.137
No, I don't want
you to bring her.

12:08.176 --> 12:09.262
Emma, maybe...

12:09.308 --> 12:11.182
this is not a safe place
for my daughter right now, dad.

12:11.206 --> 12:12.404
This is an insane place.

12:12.490 --> 12:13.680
If... if you love me...
If you love her,

12:13.704 --> 12:16.263
then you'll just keep her there.

12:17.013 --> 12:18.326
Right, and I'll deal with mom.

12:18.351 --> 12:19.607
And then I'll come home.

12:19.669 --> 12:21.551
Please, dad, just...
Just do this for me.

12:22.192 --> 12:23.504
Okay.

12:23.585 --> 12:25.896
Give her a kiss for me.
I'll check in later.

12:26.005 --> 12:27.888
Yeah, I'm sorry about mom too.

12:28.419 --> 12:29.986
Love you. Bye.

12:32.623 --> 12:34.451
You know, Em,
N-Norman's in prison.

12:34.508 --> 12:35.576
It's completely safe here.

12:35.654 --> 12:37.489
I think that maybe, you know,
it would help if...

12:37.513 --> 12:39.753
if will brought her up here.

12:40.443 --> 12:41.990
Who would it help?

12:42.318 --> 12:43.630
Me? You?

12:43.770 --> 12:46.646
No, what... what I mean is...
This is hard enough already.

12:46.747 --> 12:48.395
I'm not gonna bring
her here just so we can feel

12:48.419 --> 12:50.912
a little bit better about
Norman murdering my mother.

12:51.021 --> 12:52.721
Okay.
All right, I got it.

12:52.762 --> 12:54.017
There's no other way
to say it, Dylan.

12:54.041 --> 12:56.571
- It is what it is.
- I know.

13:11.927 --> 13:13.943
Now a bad time?

13:14.965 --> 13:17.665
Yeah, it's gonna be
a bad time for a while.

13:17.904 --> 13:20.490
I wanted to give you
an update on Norman.

13:20.639 --> 13:22.646
Look... I... I really...
I don't want an update.

13:22.732 --> 13:23.919
Okay, we...

13:24.037 --> 13:25.317
We have a lot going on right now

13:25.347 --> 13:27.162
and Norman is not
at the top of the list.

13:27.224 --> 13:29.240
Well, he should be.

13:30.607 --> 13:33.787
Emma, this is Julia.
This is Norman's lawyer.

13:34.426 --> 13:35.575
I see.

13:35.633 --> 13:37.044
Uh, is it it okay if
I step outside

13:37.088 --> 13:38.658
and talk to her
for five minutes?

13:39.185 --> 13:42.310
- About what?
- Norman's defense?

13:42.708 --> 13:45.028
He's guilty, in case
you were under any illusions.

13:45.130 --> 13:47.474
I am very sorry for the loss
of your mother, Emma.

13:47.520 --> 13:50.087
And I'm sorry your job's
now a lot harder.

13:50.685 --> 13:52.373
I know this is
a difficult time...

13:52.436 --> 13:54.996
oh, has your brother-in-law
ever killed your mother?

13:55.576 --> 13:57.560
Allegedly.

14:11.919 --> 14:13.849
Look, you, uh,
you have your money.

14:13.906 --> 14:15.446
Please, just don't...
don't involve us in this

14:15.470 --> 14:16.470
anymore, okay?

14:16.507 --> 14:19.540
They've charged him
with a capital offense, Dylan.

14:19.908 --> 14:22.238
Do you know what that means?

14:22.478 --> 14:25.431
That means he could be
facing the death penalty.

14:25.845 --> 14:28.207
Lethal injection.

14:30.282 --> 14:31.525
You know,

14:31.579 --> 14:33.710
it's one thing
to wish your brother dead

14:33.767 --> 14:36.798
and another one
to have it happen.

14:37.314 --> 14:38.775
What do you want from me?

14:38.868 --> 14:41.179
Norman has a preliminary
hearing tomorrow.

14:41.368 --> 14:42.900
I've heard
his charges are public

14:43.032 --> 14:44.485
so I'm anticipating an audience

14:44.579 --> 14:46.150
and it would look
really good for him

14:46.185 --> 14:49.254
if you were
behind him, literally.

14:49.454 --> 14:51.954
I'll hold a seat for you
behind the defense table.

14:52.517 --> 14:54.103
Look, I... I had to tell my wife

14:54.152 --> 14:56.279
that her mom was dead
this morning.

14:56.657 --> 14:59.204
Okay? And that my brother
allegedly killed her.

14:59.229 --> 15:00.997
♪♪ <i>Soft music</i>

15:01.073 --> 15:02.618
I can't do what you're asking.

15:02.678 --> 15:04.108
Yesterday, you told me
your brother

15:04.176 --> 15:06.525
belonged in
a mental institution.

15:06.993 --> 15:09.823
You said he's not bad,
he's just crazy.

15:09.907 --> 15:11.845
And I thought that
was really persuasive.

15:11.986 --> 15:13.345
I believed you.

15:13.493 --> 15:15.392
I believe you even now more

15:15.518 --> 15:17.208
that I've met Norman.

15:17.509 --> 15:20.048
But, you know, no one's
gonna want to see his illness

15:20.125 --> 15:21.759
once they see
the evidence of his crimes.

15:21.827 --> 15:24.689
They need to see
his connection to humanity.

15:24.743 --> 15:27.650
And you might not like it
right now, but that's you.

15:27.892 --> 15:29.532
You are what he's got.

15:29.768 --> 15:32.103
♪♪ <i>Somber orchestration...</i>

15:32.165 --> 15:33.946
Sorry, big brother.

15:34.194 --> 15:36.462
Sometimes it sucks to be family.

15:36.742 --> 15:38.267
Hearing's at 1:00 P.M.

15:38.477 --> 15:42.321
♪♪

15:43.846 --> 15:46.046
Can you repeat the address?

15:49.016 --> 15:52.118
- Okay.
- Okay, thanks for calling.

15:52.230 --> 15:53.460
What's up?

15:53.519 --> 15:55.519
Uh, the medical examiner called.

15:55.568 --> 15:57.766
They're releasing my mother's
remains to a funeral home.

15:57.790 --> 15:59.490
I've got to go
make the arrangements.

15:59.640 --> 16:01.603
I'll go with you.

16:03.643 --> 16:06.407
Sorry, I just
want to be on my own.

16:07.022 --> 16:08.422
Okay.

16:10.431 --> 16:12.728
Are you going to the hearing?

16:13.057 --> 16:15.087
Not if you don't want me to.

16:17.642 --> 16:20.642
I can't tell you what to do
about your family.

16:28.713 --> 16:30.073
♪♪ <i>Gentle piano music</i>

16:30.106 --> 16:32.823
How will you want to be
handling your mother's remains?

16:33.539 --> 16:35.499
I don't know, what...
What are the options?

16:35.859 --> 16:37.089
Burial or cremation.

16:37.226 --> 16:39.126
I don't know
what your finances are.

16:39.174 --> 16:40.972
Cremation is
much more economical.

16:41.036 --> 16:42.193
That'll be fine.

16:42.652 --> 16:44.956
This is your mother, correct?

16:45.072 --> 16:47.456
Biologically, yeah. I didn't
really know her that well.

16:47.524 --> 16:50.460
Sometimes those are
the hardest losses.

16:51.016 --> 16:54.116
Did she have any
religious affiliations?

16:54.269 --> 16:56.323
She belonged to
the church of herself.

16:56.441 --> 16:58.128
♪♪

16:58.223 --> 17:00.652
I understand you do most
of the local funerals.

17:00.740 --> 17:02.174
Yes, we do.

17:02.394 --> 17:04.105
Did you do Norma Bates' funeral?

17:04.134 --> 17:06.073
♪♪

17:06.159 --> 17:07.228
We did, in fact.

17:07.268 --> 17:08.355
Is... is she buried here?

17:08.380 --> 17:10.060
She was more of a mother
to me than my own.

17:10.101 --> 17:11.205
I... I regret I couldn't come.

17:11.230 --> 17:12.816
No one told me about it.

17:12.954 --> 17:14.714
She is buried here.

17:14.909 --> 17:16.425
Her son killed my mother.

17:16.580 --> 17:18.886
♪♪

17:18.977 --> 17:21.909
