21:07.407 --> 21:09.335
Uh, no, it's a '68.

21:12.221 --> 21:14.339
No, you're right.
It's... it is a '68,

21:14.393 --> 21:16.253
- all right.
- Yeah.

21:16.348 --> 21:18.378
It was the last year they, uh,

21:18.516 --> 21:19.965
did the taillights like that.

21:20.091 --> 21:22.075
Yeah, no, I know.

21:22.352 --> 21:25.379
♪ ♪

21:25.403 --> 21:28.192
♪♪

21:28.343 --> 21:31.317
- Well...
- Have a nice day.

21:31.529 --> 21:32.801
- Yeah.
- You too.

21:32.981 --> 21:36.489
♪ ♪

21:36.732 --> 21:39.732
♪♪ <i>Ominous music...</i>

21:39.838 --> 21:43.598
♪♪

21:43.653 --> 21:47.291
♪♪

22:14.947 --> 22:16.696
Don't these people
have anything better to do?

22:16.720 --> 22:18.298
Eyes front, Norman.

22:18.392 --> 22:19.915
They can't make
as many judgments

22:19.969 --> 22:21.400
about the back of your head.

22:21.464 --> 22:22.767
And remember,

22:22.946 --> 22:24.597
simple answers to the judge.

22:24.672 --> 22:25.829
Say "Your Honor."

22:25.887 --> 22:26.947
Yeah, got it.

22:37.556 --> 22:41.142
All rise.

22:41.282 --> 22:45.322
The Honorable Judge Sybil
Meredith Gollmar presiding.

22:46.906 --> 22:48.845
Please be seated
and come to order.

22:49.627 --> 22:51.111
We are here in the matter of

22:51.192 --> 22:53.111
the state of Oregon
versus Norman Bates,

22:53.194 --> 22:55.220
Docket number 386.

22:55.439 --> 22:57.629
This is a preliminary hearing.

22:57.759 --> 22:59.728
Would counsel please
identify themselves?

23:00.001 --> 23:02.301
Uh, Dan Tapley
for the state, your honor.

23:02.436 --> 23:05.455
Julia Ramos,
representing Norman Bates.

23:05.897 --> 23:07.867
Would the defendant
please stand?

23:10.407 --> 23:11.944
Are you Norman Bates,

23:12.024 --> 23:14.533
the individual named
in the complaint of this matter?

23:15.244 --> 23:18.174
Yes.
Yes, your honor.

23:18.519 --> 23:20.279
And do you authorize Julia Ramos

23:20.322 --> 23:21.664
to speak for you today?

23:21.744 --> 23:23.681
I do, your honor.

23:24.068 --> 23:26.138
You are charged
with three counts of murder

23:26.296 --> 23:27.549
in the first degree.

23:27.661 --> 23:30.181
Maximum penalty
you would face upon conviction

23:30.221 --> 23:31.259
is death.

23:31.351 --> 23:34.351
Do you understand?

23:34.494 --> 23:36.213
I do, your honor.

23:36.619 --> 23:38.541
You are entitled
to a preliminary hearing

23:38.650 --> 23:41.366
upon which the state is required
to present evidence

23:41.424 --> 23:43.174
establishing probable cause.

23:43.266 --> 23:45.166
Do you want
a probable cause hearing?

23:45.255 --> 23:46.385
We do, your honor.

23:46.486 --> 23:48.158
Is the state ready to proceed?

23:48.308 --> 23:49.782
The state is ready, your honor.

23:49.924 --> 23:51.236
Go ahead.

23:52.131 --> 23:53.321
The state calls

23:53.387 --> 23:55.717
Sheriff Jane Greene
to the stand.

24:04.877 --> 24:07.986
Dr. Jackson concluded
that Mr. Blackwell

24:08.067 --> 24:11.067
was fatally wounded
by multiple stab wounds

24:11.172 --> 24:12.299
to the neck and chest.

24:12.361 --> 24:13.525
♪♪ <i>Somber orchestration</i>

24:13.571 --> 24:16.502
And Ms. Ellis
died of strangulation.

24:16.583 --> 24:18.088
♪♪

24:18.221 --> 24:19.580
And the third victim?

24:19.900 --> 24:23.142
Sam Loomis' body
was discovered in a well.

24:23.317 --> 24:25.677
Also multiple knife wounds
to the neck and chest.

24:25.799 --> 24:28.986
He bled into his lungs
and died of Asphyxiation.

24:30.361 --> 24:32.142
♪♪

24:32.291 --> 24:35.970
So what is the link between
the victims and Norman Bates?

24:36.192 --> 24:38.392
The victims have
almost nothing in common,

24:38.494 --> 24:40.705
except for their
unfortunate encounters

24:40.869 --> 24:42.331
with the Bates Motel

24:42.470 --> 24:45.002
and with its proprietor,
Norman Bates.

24:45.186 --> 24:48.386
Jim Blackwell was in prison
with Norman's stepfather,

24:48.475 --> 24:49.611
Alex Romero.

24:49.743 --> 24:52.103
Sam Loomis was
married to a woman

24:52.213 --> 24:55.892
that Norman was infatuated with,
Madeleine Loomis.

24:56.103 --> 24:58.517
And Audrey Ellis
was the mother-in-law

24:58.627 --> 25:01.588
of Norman's brother,
Dylan Massett.

25:01.752 --> 25:05.416
♪♪

25:05.455 --> 25:09.111
♪♪

25:29.749 --> 25:31.936
I'm so sorry.

25:32.230 --> 25:34.060
Are you?

25:35.671 --> 25:37.444
Yes.

25:38.788 --> 25:41.859
I let Norman into our lives.
That was me.

25:42.054 --> 25:45.233
Sam's a piece of evidence
in there because of me.

25:45.897 --> 25:48.757
But Norman only tricked me
for a couple weeks.

25:49.223 --> 25:52.155
I mean, how did he trick you
for your whole life?

25:52.441 --> 25:55.241
♪♪ <i>Brooding orchestration...</i>

25:55.355 --> 25:57.241
♪♪

25:57.325 --> 25:59.046
You knew.

25:59.203 --> 26:01.522
You're his brother.
You knew.

26:02.100 --> 26:04.280
How can you live with yourself?

26:04.466 --> 26:08.194
♪♪

26:08.218 --> 26:11.858
♪♪

26:15.728 --> 26:18.563
♪♪ <i>Suspenseful music...</i>

26:18.732 --> 26:22.134
♪♪

26:22.548 --> 26:23.729
Where have you been?

26:23.754 --> 26:25.321
I've been worried sick
that you were

26:25.368 --> 26:26.639
dead in a ditch somewhere.

26:26.688 --> 26:28.221
- Okay, I need your... find your...
- Where have you been?

26:28.245 --> 26:29.291
It doesn't matter
where I've been.

26:29.315 --> 26:30.720
I... where's your computer?
I need to find your...

26:30.744 --> 26:31.204
why?

26:31.251 --> 26:33.868
- I... I need to go online. I need...
- Why?

26:33.924 --> 26:36.024
I need to find out
where that bastard's being held!

26:36.165 --> 26:38.181
Why didn't you tell me
Norman Bates was arrested?

26:38.378 --> 26:39.946
Because I didn't think
you needed to know...

26:39.970 --> 26:41.610
oh, come on, Maggie!

26:41.722 --> 26:44.017
Putting a bullet through
his brain is the only thing

26:44.071 --> 26:45.774
that's kept me alive
these last two years.

26:45.892 --> 26:47.696
And now I can't get at him.

26:47.751 --> 26:48.813
Alex, don't do this.

26:48.877 --> 26:51.071
- Let... let the law handle it.
- Oh, yeah, the law.

26:51.132 --> 26:52.332
Yeah, they know
what they're doing.

26:52.356 --> 26:54.181
I want him dead.
I want to do it myself.

26:54.302 --> 26:55.822
Okay, Alex, look,
you loved his mother.

26:55.899 --> 26:57.985
No mother would want that
to happen to her son.

26:58.026 --> 26:59.756
She's dead.
She doesn't have a say in it.

27:03.726 --> 27:05.920
No, Alex, please,
please, listen to me...

27:06.008 --> 27:07.368
Listen to me.

27:07.693 --> 27:10.102
You've always been
a good friend to me.

27:10.519 --> 27:13.419
My family has a cabin
in Montana that's abandoned.

27:13.454 --> 27:15.446
No, no... no, we can go there.

27:15.590 --> 27:18.336
We can assume
different identities.

27:18.554 --> 27:20.495
I know Norma's death broke you,

27:20.559 --> 27:22.389
but I can live with you broken.

27:22.496 --> 27:24.047
I can take care of you.

27:24.750 --> 27:26.274
Please, Alex,

27:26.390 --> 27:28.165
you're heading down a dark road.

27:28.207 --> 27:29.607
Let me help you.

27:29.890 --> 27:31.648
Please.

27:33.922 --> 27:36.443
All right, good-bye, Maggie.

